The Nile River north of Aswan is a popular tourist route. The Nile (Iteru in ancient Egyptian) has been a source of life for the ancient Egyptian civilization since the Stone Age. It is in its valley that all the cities of Egypt are located and almost all of its population still lives. Obukhov , Makar Mikhailovich (Tunnu) (March 16, 1902 - December 31, 1952) - Soviet statesman and party leader, participant in the Civil War, first chairman of the executive committee of the Koryak District Council of Workers' Deputies (1930-1952). He was a staunch member of the Bolshevik Party, which he joined in 14 years of age.